            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": ">so why can't checkhealth use root_dir to say which pattern matched, then report that?\n\nBecause there could be multiple `*.gpr` files in a same root directory, so `root_dir` isn't enough to know which one is being used by the ada language server. In such a case, clients will often use `workspace/didChangeConfiguration` to select a `.gpr` file, but storing and re-displaying that information would not work in cases where the client let the server choose a `.gpr` file.",
